  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring a Clean Environment in Collective Centers: Gaza</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) 21,400 individuals (regardless of their refugee status) staying in 14 collective centers have access to sufficient potable and non-potable water during one month (target 26liters/day/person)

2) Desalination plants for six wells will be installed

3) Emergency maintenance will continue for 14 collective centers (including stands, pipes and fittings)

4) WASH staff are trained in emergency water and sanitation practices, collective center management, solid waste management, and hygiene promotion and response. These trainings are vital for prevention of disease outbreak in collective centers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will ensure that families displaced to the UNRWA collective centers - due to the uninhabitable conditions of the houses - live in an environment with reduced risk of water and sanitation related diseases and health hazards.</narrative>
  </description>
